# Normalize line endings so the committed dist/ bundles never show a spurious
# "modified" status on Windows checkouts (where git would otherwise want CRLF).
# dist/ is checked into git and run as-is by the plugin, so its bytes must be
# stable across platforms and match what CI's `npm run build` produces on Linux.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never touch their bytes.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
